 in British Columbia. Comparative material is supplied in an article on the ramifications of a national wages policy in Britain. This volume also contains the concluding part of an article on international fisheries which appeared in the first volume of this series.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aSocial problems. 0aSociological jurisprudence. 7aLAW / Essays.2bisacsh1 aArthurs, H. W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaulieu, Marie-Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrispo, J. H. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrank, W. F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerbert, Raymond G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, D. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMackay, R. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, E.E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRand, I. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757774240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487577742423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487577742.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK